Our engineers need to urgently install a new piece of equipment, called a substation, on the electricity network along Hempstead Lane. This equipment controls and delivers the electricity into your area. These are essential works that will improve the reliability of the electricity network and ensure our network can uphold the amount of electricity in your area. During this time you will be connected to a generator to provide you electricity whilst we carry out our essential works. In order to connect and disconnect the generator safely we will need to temporarily switch off your power. We aim to connect and disconnect the generator within 1 hour so your power may come on sooner. The government has given exemptions to certain industries and activities, this outage falls into this category.
